    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>smoky squash purée</strong> to the orzo with 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[400ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and cook, covered, stirring frequently, for 10-12 min or until the orzo is cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Tip: Stirring the orzo will release the starch from the pasta, making it creamier! If your pan starts to look a little dry, just add a splash more water</p><p>Once the orzo is done, wash then add your <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min further, stirring until the spinach has wilted</p>",
